rset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1340–":"about 1340–Deceased","1340–Male":"1340–Deceased","1374–Male":"1374–Deceased","1310–Male":"1310–Deceased","1310":"1310","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","about 1340":"about 1340","Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kirkham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (mainly northwestern): habitational name from any of the places in Lancashire and East Yorkshire named Kirkham. The placenames derive from Old Norse <i>kirkja</i> ‘church’ + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’ or Old Norse <i>heim</i> ‘homestead, estate’.","Possibly an altered form of German <b>Kirchham</b>, a habitational name from either of two places called Kirchham, in Austria or Bavaria."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Kirkham was born about 1340, in Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom as the son of Nicholas Kirkham. He had at least 1 son. He died in Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1340–":"umbes 1340–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1374–Male":"1374–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1310":"1310","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Axbridge, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1340–":"noin 1340–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1374–Male":"1374–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1310":"1310","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","about 1340":"noin 1340","Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Axbridge, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1340–":"environ 1340–Décédé","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1374–Male":"1374–Décédé","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1310":"1310","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","about 1340":"environ 1340","Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Axbridge, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Kirkham est né environ 1340, à Axbridge, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Nicholas Kirkham. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé à Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"about 1340–":"um 1340–Verstorben","1340–Male":"1340–Verstorben","1374–Male":"1374–Verstorben","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","1310":"1310","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","about 1340":"um 1340","Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert Kirkham wurde um 1340 in Axbridge, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, als Sohn von 